name: 23S rRNA (uridine2552-2'-O)-methyltransferase
reaction: S-adenosyl-L-methionine + uridine2552 in 23S rRNA = S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + 2'-O-methyluridine2552 in 23S rRNA
comment: The enzyme catalyses the 2'-O-methylation of the universally conserved U2552 in the A loop of 23S rRNA [3].

references.title: The FtsJ/RrmJ heat shock protein of Escherichia coli is a 23 S ribosomal RNA methyltransferase.
